extends /shared/layout
block append endscripts
   script(src="/lib/accordion.js")
block content
   +pageTitle
   +pod('')
      .uk-width-1-1
         p
            | Only a few types of aneuploidy are compatible with life. Trisomy 21 (a cause of Down Syndrome) is relatively common, as are conditions involving extra or missing sex chromosomes. 
      .uk-container.uk-container-center
         .uk-grid
            .uk-width-medium-1-1
               p Genetic disorders resulting from monoploidy include:
               #ac.uk-accordion(data-uk-accordion="{showfirst: false}")
                  h3.uk-accordion-title 45, XO (Turner Syndrome)
                  .uk-accordion-content
                     .uk-width-medium-1-1
                        include ./turner/index.pug
      .uk-container.uk-container-center
         .uk-grid
            .uk-width-medium-1-1
               p Genetic disorders resulting from polyploidy include:
               #ac.uk-accordion(data-uk-accordion="{showfirst: false}")
                  h3.uk-accordion-title Trisomy 21 (Down Syndrome)
                  .uk-accordion-content
                     include ./down/index.pug
                  h3.uk-accordion-title 47, XXY (Klinefelter Syndrome)
                  .uk-accordion-content
                     include ./klinefelter/index.pug
   
   
   +references
      p Risk for Down Syndrome: Cuckle HS, Wald NJ, Thompson SG. Estimating a woman's risk of having a pregnancy associated with Down's syndrome using her age and serum alpha-fetoprotein level. Br J Obstet Gynaecol. 1987;94:387–402.
   
      p Genetics home reference: https://ghr.nlm.nih.gov/primer/mutationsanddisorders/structuralchanges
   
   block append endscripts
      script(src="/lib/slideshow.js")
      script(src="/lib/slideshow-fx.js")
